# API keys for keyed tool backends — copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in.
# Loaded at boot by core/credentials.py; an unset key is fine, it just means
# that backend reports "no key configured" instead of running.
#
# Nothing is required today: the default search backend (duckduckgo) and all
# current tools (time, weather via Open-Meteo, Wikipedia) are keyless. These
# names are reserved for future keyed backends behind BaseSearch.
# TAVILY_API_KEY=
# BRAVE_API_KEY=
